      <hedline>
        <hl1>Goodby, Silverstein Shuffles Executives</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jeri Clausing</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Clausing, Jeri</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Goodby, Silverstein &amp; Partners is reorganizing as its co-chairmen and co-creative directors, Jeff Goodby and Rich Silverstein hand over day-to-day creative duties to Steve Simpson and Paul Venables (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Goodby, Silverstein &amp; Partners in San Francisco, part of the Omnicom Group, is reorganizing as its co-chairmen and co-creative directors, Jeff Goodby, 48, and Rich Silverstein, 51, hand over their day-to-day creative duties to Steve Simpson and Paul Venables. Mr. Goodby confirmed a report of the shift this week in Advertising Age. Mr. Simpson, 40, is a partner and creative director, and Mr. Venables, 34, is associate partner and creative director.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Goodby, Silverstein &amp; Partners in San Francisco, part of the Omnicom Group, is reorganizing as its co-chairmen and co-creative directors, Jeff Goodby, 48, and Rich Silverstein, 51, hand over their day-to-day creative duties to Steve Simpson and Paul Venables. Mr. Goodby confirmed a report of the shift this week in Advertising Age. Mr. Simpson, 40, is a partner and creative director, and Mr. Venables, 34, is associate partner and creative director.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
